1. Use TypeScript strict mode for all new code
2. Follow React functional component patterns with arrow functions
3. Use Tailwind CSS with mobile-first approach (default → md: → lg: breakpoints)
4. File naming conventions:
   - Components: PascalCase.tsx
   - Types: camelCase.types.ts
   - Utils: camelCase.utils.ts
   - Hooks: useCase.ts
5. Component structure:
   - Imports grouped: React/external first, then internal
   - Types/interfaces at the top
   - Props interface with 'Props' suffix
6. Commit messages follow conventional commits:
   - feat: for features
   - fix: for bug fixes
   - style: for styling changes
   - refactor: for code improvements
7. Always implement responsive design for:
   - Mobile (default)
   - Tablet (md:)
   - Desktop (lg:)
8. Use semantic HTML elements for better accessibility
9. Keep bundle size optimized - lazy load heavy components
10. Don't modify:
    - public/investim-logo.svg
    - package.json versions
11. Required testing:
    - Components: React Testing Library
    - User interactions
    - Responsive behavior
12. Performance guidelines:
    - Memoize expensive computations
    - Optimize images
    - Minimize re-renders
13. Use React Router for navigation
14. Use HeroIcons for icons
15. Use React Hook Form for form handling
16. Use Vite for development
17. Use ESLint and Prettier for code formatting